Helen's Dead is a 2023 American comedy mystery film directed by K. Asher Levin for a screenplay by Amy Brown Carver and story she co-wrote with Levin.  It stars Annabelle Dexter-Jones, Tyrese Gibson, Emile Hirsch, Dylan Gelula and Oliver Cooper.[1][2]


Plot[edit]

Production[edit]
Principal photography took place in Santa Fe, New Mexico in December 2021.[3] In February 2022, the film entered in post-production.[4]

Release[edit]
In September 2023, Screen Media acquired all North American distribution rights and set a release for November 3, 2023, in the "top 10 markets".[6]

Reception[edit]
On the review aggregator website Rotten Tomatoes, 17% of 6 critics' reviews are positive, with an average rating of 3.6/10.[7]
